The paper deals with mechanism design for combinatorial auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves Bayesian settings and approximation algorithms, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The paper also presents a generalization of prophet inequalities, which is a topic in online learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with multi-agent systems and auctions, which is a topic in multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
